Class CopyOnWriteArrayListMultimap<K,V>

java.lang.Object
  org.whispercomm.c2dm4j.util.CopyOnWriteArrayListMultimap<K,V>
Type Parameters:
K - the type of the keys held in this map
V - the type of the values held in this map
All Implemented Interfaces:
ListMultimap<K,V>, Multimap<K,V>
public class CopyOnWriteArrayListMultimap<K,V>
extends Object
implements ListMultimap<K,V>

A thread-safe implementation of ListMultimap in which all mutative operations are applied to a copy of the underlying ArrayListMultimap.

These copies are expensive, but may be acceptable when reads vastly outnumber writes (i.e., mutative operations). Reads are non-blocking. Iterators see a "snapshot" of the map at the time the iterator was created and may not modify the map (e.g., add and remove are not supported. Writes are ordered by a lock and thus are blocking.

Author:
David R. Bild
